Peazi was good, a little salty but quite flavorful. The fry was a bit lackluster but not horrible. The veggie samosa was very good. Delicious & crunchy but not too fried. The garlic naan was good but only 1 piece was really garlicky. The basmati rice was also good. The biggest let down was the chicken tikka Masala. It wasn’t bad but wasn’t good. The sauce while creamy, was too thin & too sweet; it lacked depth and the chicken was a little dry. I wouldn’t get this dish again but I would come back & try something else.  The sanitation practices are questionable but the food is decent. Service wasn’t amazing but also wasn’t bad.
